The paper presents a distributed algorithm for finding Hamiltonian cycles in random graphs, which involves distributed computation and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the study of random graphs, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves network analysis and communication complexity, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
